@lanchengx

here's a [proposal](https://wonderfull.feishu.cn/docs/doccn4a1x4Rmx4pEADYbtkAeLGc) for this issue. as @zhfeng has pointed out: XA statements should be passed to backend database instead of wrapping it into JTA. Having discussion with @jingshanglu a litter bit more, we both agree to firstly focus on supporting XA statements on a single database, and throw error when multiple instance configured.

and I think @zhfeng 's pr https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/pull/13362 has get most of job done, I think we only need to have more discussion on inXA and transactionType.MANUAL.

@zhfeng I've invite u to join shardingsphere slack channel, so that we can have a conversation online, or we can use any other im tools u like.

> Is this right?

Yes, it is right. 
@lanchengx, please help to review, thanks~

@oneslideicywater 
Yes, I got it.
Your ShardingSphere-Proxy need data source configuration to connect to Postgres server, so the param should be added to the url of Proxy's config file.  Like `config-sharidng.yaml`.
